title: Andrew Tate loses latest appeal to be released from Romanian prison amid human trafficking case
description: Andrew Tate's appeal against a 30-day extension of his detention in Romania has been denied by a court, meaning the social media influencer will remain in prision.

title: 'Everything is mystical': Mexican president shares photo of 'mythological woodland alux' on Twitter
description: The Mexican president posted a photo of what he thought was a mythological 'alux' on social media, adding "everything is mystical".

title: Ex-relatives in court over Hong Kong model's murder after body parts found in fridge and cooking pot
description: The ex-husband, former brother-in-law and former father-in-law of a Hong Kong model have appeared in court charged with her murder after her legs were found in a fridge.

title: 'Everything is bombed here': Inside the town of Vuhledar on Ukraine's frontline
description: The scarred and battered mining town of Vuhledar sits perched on a hill in the Donetsk region.

title: Peter Obi takes Lagos in Nigeria's closest ever presidential election
description: Votes are still being counted in the closest run presidential election in Nigeria's history.

title: New 5.6 magnitude earthquake strikes Turkey, killing one and injuring over 100
description: A new 5.6 magnitude earthquake has struck Turkey, killing one person and injuring 110, according to authorities.

title: First inmates transferred to El Salvador 'mega prison' in crackdown on gangs
description: Thousands of inmates have started to be transferred to one of the world's largest prisons in El Salvador.

title: Football fans throw thousands of soft toys on pitch for children affected by Turkey-Syria quake
description: Besiktas fans threw thousands of stuffed toys onto the pitch during a match on Sunday to donate to children affected by the earthquake in Turkey and Syria.

title: Winter sports are 'nailing lid on own coffin' by accepting sponsorship from polluters
description: The sponsorship of winter competitions by energy hungry firms like British Airways and Volvo are "nailing the lid" on the sports' "own coffin", a British Olympic champion has said.

title: COVID most likely leaked from Wuhan lab, says US Energy Department
description: The COVID -19 virus most likely leaked from a laboratory in Wuhan, according to the US Energy Department.

title: Volodymyr Zelenskyy sacks top Ukrainian commander without giving a reason
description: Volodymyr Zelenskyy has sacked one of his top Ukrainian military commanders, but has not said why.
